THE 2010 FIFA World Cup staged in South Africa was described as one of the organisation by then president Sepp Blatter. Mzansi managed to silence doubters by pulling off a successful showpiece, the first World Cup on Africa soil. The atmosphere was second to none with South Africans showcasing their colourful tradition to the rest of the world. Mzansi's World Cup also had loads of action on the pitch matching the electric atmosphere. There was no lack of goals, beautiful ones at that. Siphiwe Tshabalala kicked things off with his stunner against Mexico in their opening match at the FNB Stadium. There were more stunners to follow. Check out the Top Ten goals of the 2010 Word Cup below: 